11/07/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu urged Britain on Monday (10 July) to consider the possibility of a liberalised visa regime for Romanian citizens. 
His statement followed a meeting with his Czech counterpart, Vaclav Klaus, in Bucharest. 
Among other things, the two discussed the US Senate debate on easing the US visa regime for Romanian and Czech citizens. 
Basescu said he expects a similar move in London. 
For his part, Klaus expressed confidence that Romania would become an EU member in 2007, as scheduled. 
(Romania Libera, Bucharest Daily News - 11/07/06; Rompres - 10/07/06)
